    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a pristine 2011 BMW M3 Coupe (E92) equipped with the ZCP Competition Package. This specimen is powered by the legendary S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8, an engine featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system, delivering a linear power band up to its 8,400 RPM redline. Power is managed via a tactile 6-speed manual gearbox and a GKN-sourced M Variable Differential Lock. The chassis is sharpened by Electronic Damper Control (EDC) with ZCP-specific mapping and a 10mm reduction in ride height. This vehicle has undergone meticulous mechanical stewardship, with documented preventative replacement of the rod bearings and throttle actuators. The exterior retains its factory-original Alpine White finish with zero stone chips or swirl marks, while the interior Novillo leather is free of bolster compression or UV-induced fading. A true collector-grade example of the final naturally aspirated M3.",
      "price": 48500.0,
